sentences: Monic Gabrielle Cecconi-Botella (born 30 September 1936) is a French pianist, music educator and composer.
In 1983, she became a professor of music analysis at the Paris Conservatoire.
In 1966, Cecconi-Botella won a First at the Prix de Rome.
In 2008, she founded the Festival Seasons of the Voice in Gordes, Provence.
